<P>
Photo, Protesters Block Federal Building About 100 protesters marched Thursday 
from the county art museum to the downtown Federal Building, where 27 linked 
arms and blocked the entrance in a non-violent demonstration for artistic 
freedom and against attempts in Congress to put rigid controls on which works 
of art the National Endowment for the Arts can support. Police arrested all 27, 
who paid $25 fines and were released. MINDY SCHAUER / For The Times 
</P>
