<TEXT>
<P>
Shane Mosley of Pomona and Oscar de la Hoya of Los Angeles advanced to title 
matches in the U. S. Amateur Boxing Championships at Colorado Springs, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
Mosley, 18, mixed counterpunching with aggression in outclassing Daniel Lujan 
of Alinas, 5-0, in a 132-pound bout. The 17-year-old de la Hoya stopped 
Sandtanner Lewis of Miami with a right to the body at 2:30 of the first round 
in a 125-pound battle of high school students. 
</P>
