<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Your Way Out: The major TV networks agreed Wednesday to jointly conduct exit 
polls and project winners on Election Day to save money and lessen the 
competitive pressure to call a race before the polls close in the West. CNN, 
which has not conducted exit polls before, joined ABC, CBS and NBC in the 
consortium, to be known as Voter Research and Surveys. The organization will 
survey a random sampling of voters as they leave polling places each Election 
Day, providing its findings on local, state and national races to the networks 
and other media. BETH KLEID 
</P>
