<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FOUR PLEAD NO CONTEST IN 'SKINHEAD' ASSAULT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four people accused of making racial slurs and assaulting an Iranian couple 
last May in a La Verne supermarket parking lot have pleaded no contest in 
Pomona Superior Court. Police said the four looked like "skinheads" and were 
carrying "white power" cards. 
</P>
<P>
Timothy Robert Zaal, 25, of Glendora was sentenced to a year in County Jail and 
three years' probation and Scott Robert Wilson, 28, of West Covina received 180 
days in jail and three years' probation after each pleaded to a charge of 
felony assault. 
</P>
<P>
William Killackey, 21, of Covina was sentenced to 120 days in jail and two 
years' probation after pleading to a misdemeanor battery charge. His sister, 
Amy, 19, of Yorba Linda was sentenced to 34 days in jail and two years' 
probation on the same charge. 
</P>
<P>
The victims testified that they were walking to their car when the defendants 
followed them, and, apparently thinking they were Jewish, made anti-Semitic 
remarks and fought with them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
