<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: COUNTYWIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man charged with holding up 17 businesses, mostly Blockbuster video stores, 
pleaded guilty Thursday to 14 counts of armed robbery. 
</P>
<P>
Roberto Cruz Loza, 31, of San Diego changed his plea just before his 
preliminary hearing was to begin. 
</P>
<P>
Municipal Judge Charles Patrick then set sentencing for March 29. Loza faces a 
maximum sentence of 33 years in state prison and a $20,000 fine. 
</P>
<P>
The robberies ranged from San Marcos to National City, and lasted from Sept. 26 
to Dec. 26. All but one of the stores were Blockbusters. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Steve Anear had subpoenaed 24 witnesses to testify Thursday 
and today for the preliminary hearing. He said Loza had a prior conviction for 
robbery and was released on parole last April. 
</P>
<P>
Loza remains in County Jail in lieu of $250,000 bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
