</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bank of New England Put Under Limits: In trouble because of a large portfolio 
of bad real estate loans, the banking firm handed over significant control to 
federal regulators. The regulators ordered the Boston-based institution to 
suspend all dividend payments and come up with a plan within 30 days to get it 
and its subsidiaries back on sound footing. Meanwhile, all dividend payments 
have been halted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
