<P>
RANCHO SANTIAGO ROLLS PAST CYPRESS, 12-4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CYPRESS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore Jerry Aschoff allowed four hits and an unearned run in seven innings 
to help Rancho Santiago College to a 12-4 victory over Cypress Thursday in an 
Orange Empire Conference baseball game at Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress' first run came in the fifth inning and was helped along by an error 
and wild pitch. 
</P>
<P>
Aschoff walked two and had five strikeouts. 
</P>
<P>
"He was definitely the key today," Rancho Santiago Coach Don Sneddon said. "He 
did a good job of getting his breaking ball over the plate. That is something 
he has struggled with in earlier games this season." 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago took a first-inning lead on a home run by Steve Grack. The Dons 
added a run in the fourth on back-to-back doubles by Conrad Colby and Marty 
Neff. Rancho Santiago (13-2 and 3-0 in conference play) scored three more in 
the fifth, one in the seventh and six in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
Grack had three hits and scored three runs. Terry Tewell had three hits, 
including a double, for Cypress (11-5, 0-2). STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
