<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
US Facilities Corp.: The Costa Mesa insurance and reinsurance holding company 
reported that higher net investment income and premium increases contributed to 
net income of $2.1 million for 1989, contrasted with a loss of $4.7 million for 
1988. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue increased 54%, to $62.9 million from $40.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the fourth quarter, the company reported net income of $791,000, contrasted 
with a loss of nearly $3 million for the comparable 1988 quarter. Revenue rose 
48%, to $17.5 million from $11.9 million. 
</P>
