<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
THATCHER FARES POORLY IN POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The political fortunes of Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher plunged further 
today with the release of an opinion poll showing her Conservative Party 18.5% 
behind the opposition Labor Party, its lowest standing in 19 years. 
</P>
<P>
The survey undertaken by Gallup for the Daily Telegraph newspaper indicated 
that Thatcher's slide is due to a controversial new tax and her refusal to 
lower interest rates to spur economic growth. 
</P>
<P>
It showed 65% of people are dissatisfied with Thatcher as prime minister. 
</P>
<P>
The poll put the Labor Party of Neil Kinnock at 49.5%, a rise of 1.5% from two 
previous polls. 
</P>
<P>
It placed the Conservatives at 31%, their lowest standing since September, 
1971. 
</P>
<P>
The centrist Liberal Democrats have 7%, the environmentalist Green party 5.5% 
and others 7%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
