<P>
EX-JUDGE TO INVESTIGATE PIERCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former federal Judge Arlin M. Adams was appointed today to investigate 
allegations that former Housing Secretary Samuel R. Pierce Jr. and top aides 
illegally steered government rent subsidies to politically connected 
developers. 
</P>
<P>
Adams was appointed an independent counsel by a special court to investigate 
allegations that Pierce and top aides at the Department of Housing and Urban 
Development conspired to defraud the Moderate Rehabilitation Program. 
</P>
<P>
Adams, who served 17 years as a member of the U.S. 3rd Circuit Court of Appeals 
in Philadelphia, is a lawyer in that city and chairman of the board of 
directors of the University of Pennsylvania Law School. 
